UNITED STATES, Plaintiff in Error, v. GOOD SPRINGS ANCHOR COMPANY and Fidelity & Deposit Company of Maryland, Defendants in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 27, 1929. No. 5422. Samuel W. McNabb, U. S. Atty., and Emmett E. Doherty, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. Claude I. Parker and Ralph W. Smith, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for defendants in error.

Before RUDKIN, DIETRICH, and HUNT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed on authority of United States v. John Barth Co. and United States Fidelity & Guaranty Co., 49 S. Ct. 366, 73 L. Ed.-, decided by the Supreme Court May 13, 1929.
